1 25–1002.
2 (a) There is a beauty salon beer [and], wine, AND LIQUOR license.
3 (b) The Board may issue the license to a holder of a beauty salon permit issued
4 under § 5–501 of the Business Occupations and Professions Article.
5 (c) The license authorizes the license holder to provide not more than 12 OUNCES
6 OF BEER, 5 ounces of [beer or] wine [by the glass], OR 1.7 OUNCES OF LIQUOR for
7 on–premises consumption by a beauty salon customer:
8 (1) when the customer is provided a cosmetology service under § 5–101(n)
9 of the Business Occupations and Professions Article; or
10 (2) while the customer is attending a fund–raising event at the beauty
11 salon for which the County Department of Permitting Services has issued a permit.
12 (d) The license may not be transferred to another location.
13 (e) The license holder may provide beer [and], wine, AND LIQUOR during normal
14 business hours but not later than 9 p.m.
15 (f) An establishment for which the license is issued is subject to the alcohol
16 awareness training requirements under § 4–505 of this article.
17 (g) The annual license fee is $100.
18 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
19 1, 2025.

